  <data key="d17">ries of birds or of any animals, or the sneezing of men , or the sudden movements of limbs, this belongs in general to "augury," which is so called from the chattering of birds [avium garritu], just as "auspice" is derived from watching birds [avium inspectione]. These are chiefly wont</data>
