  <data key="d13">sin_type</data>
  <data key="d14">ann.concept-sortilege-species-of-concept-divination-st-ii-ii-q095-a003-resp</data>
  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q095.a003.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">rving who throws the highest score; or by observing what catches the eye when one opens a book, all of which are named "sortilege." Accordingly it is clear that there are three kinds of divination . The first is when the demons are invoked openly, this comes under the head of "necromancy"</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
<edge source="concept.superstition" target="concept.religion" id="edge.concept.superstition.excess_opposed_to.concept.religion">
