  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">ought not, and in like manner as regards other circumstances, as the Philosopher shows (Ethic. iv, 1,2,3). Accordingly superstition is a vice contrary to religion by excess, not that it offers more to the divine worship than true religion, but because it offers divine worship either to whom it ought not, or in a manner it ought no</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
