  <data key="d16">explicit_textual</data>
  <data key="d17">according to the precepts of God the object of that worship: and to this must be referred the superstition of certain "observances." Augustine alludes to these three (De Doctr. Christ. ii, 20), where he says that "anything invented by man for making and worshipping idols is superstitious , | of the malice of the demons , who strive to entangle men's minds with such like trifles. Accordingly it is evident that all these observances are superstitious and unlawful: they are apparently remains of idolatry , which authorized the observance of auguries, of lucky and unlucky days which is allied to divination by</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
